The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object detection and image classification, which are primarily covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves fusing decisions from two different types of computer vision tasks, which can be seen as a machine learning approach. Therefore, it can also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which suggests that it involves experimental evaluation, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
